"32:20:11" : {s: 32, a: 20, w: 11, r: "عود", t: "أُعِيدُوا۟", l: "أُعِيدُ", lc: 18, tl: "uʿīdū", lb: "পুনরায় করা",e: "they (will) be returned", b: "", f: 0, rm: "to return, turn away, come back, repeat, restore. aidun - one who returns. maadun - place where one returns, another name of Makkah. aada (vb. 4) - to cause to return, restore. The verb aada is transitive to mean to get some one return or cause to return or bring back (what has passed away)."},
